definitions.definition: The principal church serving as the office (and some as place of residence) of an archdiocese 's/a diocese 's archbishop / bishop which is symbolized by an episcopal throne known as the cathedra .
A large or important church building.
A large, impressive, lofty, and/or important building or place of some other kind.
A large buttressed structure built by certain termites .

main_definition: The principal church serving as the office (and some as place of residence) of an archdiocese 's/a diocese 's archbishop / bishop which is symbolized by an episcopal throne known as the cathedra .
secondary_definitions: ( loosely or informally ) A large or important church building.
( figurative ) A large, impressive, lofty, and/or important building or place of some other kind.
A large buttressed structure built by certain termites .
